conversation.content: Workflow image uploaded. Ask me to analyze it when you are ready.
Analyzing the uploaded workflow image to extract inputs and outputs.
Analysis ready. Review inputs and outputs, then approve or ask for refinement.

I spotted a few ambiguities in the diagram:
- Ambiguities: Exact data fields contained in 'Clinician Input' are not specified.; Criteria used by the 'Accept/Reject Gate' are not defined in the diagram.; What happens on the Reject branch is not visually shown (no outgoing arrow).; Whether Consent & Context check can block the process before Patient Management Agent is unclear.; Error/failure handling for MCP reads (consent, medical knowledge, EHR/FHIR, scheduling/messaging) is not shown.; Which actions trigger scheduling (is scheduling always the next step, or only for certain clinician requests?) is not explicit.
- Questions: What specific action types can a clinician initiate (e.g., schedule-only vs. record update vs. treatment change)?; What exact rules/criteria govern the Accept/Reject decision (policy, consent, clinical safety, resource availability)?; Can the Consent & Context Agent stop the workflow if consent is invalid or missing, and how is that surfaced?; Is the Scheduling Agent always invoked after acceptance, or only when the proposal includes appointments?; What fields are required for scheduling (e.g., appointment type, location, provider, time window)?; How are audit events structured and what minimum fields must be logged to Provenance MCP?
- Warnings: Multiple terminal MCP boxes exist; make sure downstream systems treat these as actions/endpoints rather than intermediate steps.; The diagram implies reads and proposed changes to EHR/FHIR but does not show explicit commit/rollback logic.; The Reject path likely ends after logging, but the absence of a terminal box for reject could cause interpretation differences.
Reply with clarification or ask me to refine the analysis.

analysis.workflow_description: An agentic orchestration flow that takes a clinician’s request, checks consent and policy context, consults medical knowledge, manages and proposes patient record changes, gates those changes for acceptance or rejection, and if accepted, schedules and messages while auditing every action.

inputs.name: clinician_action_type
inputs.description: The primary intent of the clinician’s request.
inputs.constraints: Must be one of the enumerated values.

inputs.name: patient_id
inputs.description: Unique identifier for the patient whose record or schedule is involved.
inputs.constraints: Alphanumeric; must correspond to an existing EHR/FHIR record.

inputs.name: clinician_id
inputs.description: Identifier for the clinician initiating the action.
inputs.constraints: Must map to a valid provider in the system.

inputs.name: encounter_datetime
inputs.description: The date and time of the clinical encounter or request.
inputs.constraints: Must be a valid ISO-8601 timestamp.

inputs.name: consent_status
inputs.description: Indicates whether required patient consents covering the requested action are currently valid.
inputs.constraints: If false, the workflow may halt or require policy override.

inputs.name: consent_scope
inputs.description: The domain(s) of consent applicable to the requested action.
inputs.constraints: Must include scopes covering the proposed changes or scheduling.

inputs.name: policy_violation_detected
inputs.description: Flag indicating whether the requested action conflicts with organizational or regulatory policy.
inputs.constraints: If true, action should be rejected or routed for override.

inputs.name: medical_knowledge_reference
inputs.description: Identifier or pointer to guidelines or medical knowledge consulted for the request.
inputs.constraints: Should correspond to a valid entry in the Medical Knowledge MCP.

inputs.name: ehr_patient_record
inputs.description: The patient’s record as read from EHR/FHIR MCP used to evaluate and propose changes.
inputs.constraints: Must be valid FHIR-conformant data structure.

inputs.name: patient_management_proposal_status
inputs.description: Outcome classification from the Patient Management Agent indicating if a scheduling step should proceed.

inputs.name: appointment_type
inputs.description: Type of appointment requested for scheduling.

inputs.name: appointment_start_datetime
inputs.description: Desired start time for the appointment.
inputs.constraints: Must be in the future relative to encounter_datetime for routine scheduling.

inputs.name: location_or_service_site
inputs.description: Clinic location or service site for the appointment.
inputs.constraints: Must be valid in the scheduling system.

inputs.name: preferred_communication_channel
inputs.description: Channel used to notify patient about the scheduled appointment.
inputs.constraints: Must be supported by the Messaging MCP and comply with consent.

inputs.name: accept_decision
inputs.description: Whether proposed changes and scheduling should proceed.
inputs.constraints: True proceeds to Scheduling Agent; False stops progression.

inputs.name: audit_required
inputs.description: Indicates that every action must be logged to the append-only audit.

decision_points.name: Accept/Reject Gate
decision_points.description: Determines whether the Patient Management Agent’s proposed changes (and any scheduling) should proceed.
decision_points.condition: Proceed only if accept_decision == true AND consent_status == true AND policy_violation_detected == false AND patient_management_proposal_status == 'ready_for_scheduling'

branches.condition: accept_decision == true AND consent_status == true AND policy_violation_detected == false AND patient_management_proposal_status == 'ready_for_scheduling'
accept_decision == false OR consent_status == false OR policy_violation_detected == true OR patient_management_proposal_status != 'ready_for_scheduling'
branches.outcome: Do not schedule; end after logging.

outputs.name: Provenance MCP (Audit every action)
outputs.description: Append-only audit log entry created for each workflow action.

outputs.name: Consent/Policy MCP
outputs.description: Read/check of patient consent and applicable policy context.

outputs.name: Medical Knowledge MCP
outputs.description: Consultation of medical knowledge/guidelines relevant to the request.

outputs.name: EHR/FHIR MCP (Patient Data System)
outputs.description: Read patient data and propose changes to EHR/FHIR.

outputs.name: Scheduling/Messaging MCP
outputs.description: Schedule appointments and send patient notifications/messages.

workflow_paths.description: Standard successful path: consent valid, policies clear, proposal accepted, schedule created and patient notified.
Rejected proposal or unmet policy/consent: audit only, no scheduling.
decision_sequence: Accept/Reject Gate -> accept_decision == false OR consent_status == false OR policy_violation_detected == true OR proposal_status != 'ready_for_scheduling'

workflow_paths.description: Consent check fails early; action halted after audit logging.
decision_sequence: Accept/Reject Gate -> consent_status == false (implicit stop before scheduling)

workflow_paths.description: Successful scheduling plus patient record update loop: scheduling completes and records are updated in EHR/FHIR.
